# ūüĆź WebUI Endpoint Inventory Plan (Film-Review template)

## ūüéĮ Objective

Determine which backend endpoints are required to fully support the `Film-Review-Movie-Database` template in `dalogin-quarkus/src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/film-review`, and define how to extend the current WebUI scope in controlled phases.

This is a planning artifact for endpoint coverage and scope expansion, not a rewrite plan.

Role ownership
- Web routes/templates and endpoint matrix: `@frontend-dev`
- Backend API ownership and contract confirmation: `@backend-dev`
- SQL/data contract checks for catalog/discovery queries: `@database-dev`
- Environment and rollout checks for exposed routes and ingress: `@devops`
- Client contract parity checks for shared endpoint changes: `@ios-dev`

---

## 1) Baseline (as implemented now)

Current Angular app entrypoint:
- `dalogin-quarkus/src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/film-review/app.js`

Current backend bases used by WebUI:
- `LOGIN`: `/login` (dalogin-quarkus)
- `BOOK`: `/mbooks-1/rest/book` (mbooks-quarkus)
- `IMAGE`: `/simple-service-webapp/webapi/myresource` (simple-service-webapp-quarkus)

Current route coverage in WebUI:
- `/login`
- `/change-password`
- `/movies`
- `/venues-list`
- `/venue-movies/:locationId`
- `/venues/:movieId`
- `/dates/:locationId/:movieId`
- `/checkout`
- `/purchases`
- `/purchases/:purchaseId`

---

## 2) Endpoint inventory needed by current booking flow (P1)

### 2.1 Auth + account (`/login`)

Required by templates/controllers:
- `POST /HelloWorld` (login)
- `POST /forgotPSw`
- `POST /forgotPSwCode`
- `POST /forgotPSwNewPSw`
- `GET /logout`

Purchase/payment bridge endpoints used by film-review app:
- `GET /CheckOut` (Braintree client token)
- `POST /CheckOut` (full checkout)
- `GET /GetAllPurchases`
- `GET /ManagePurchases?purchaseId=...`
- `POST /ManagePurchases` (cancel tickets or delete purchase)

### 2.2 Booking/catalog (`/mbooks-1/rest/book`)

Required by templates/controllers:
- `GET /movies`
- `GET /locations`
- `GET /venue/v2/{movieId}`
- `GET /venue/movies?locationId=...`
- `GET /dates/{locationId}/{movieId}`
- `GET /seats/{screeningDateId}`

### 2.3 Images (`/simple-service-webapp/webapi/myresource`)

Required for posters/location images:
- Existing image URLs built from `movie.large_picture`, `movie.thumbnail_picture`, `venues_picture`, `location.thumbnail`.

---

## 3) Gap analysis for Film-Review template pages

Template repository contains additional pages (blog/news/celebrity/profile/rating) beyond current booking routes.

### 3.1 Covered now
- Login + password reset
- Movie browse/search (client-side filter)
- Venue/date/seat selection
- Checkout + purchases history/details

### 3.2 Not covered yet (endpoint gaps)

A) Movie details enrichment
- Need endpoint for one movie detail with richer metadata (cast, runtime, trailer, rating history).
- Candidate: `GET /mbooks-1/rest/book/movies/{movieId}` (new).

B) Trending/discovery blocks in template
- Need endpoint for homepage widgets.
- Candidate: `GET /mbooks-1/rest/book/trending-movies` (planned in BackendEndpoints).

C) Categories/date navigation server-side filtering
- Need endpoint-level filtering to reduce payload size and make pagination deterministic.
- Candidate:
  - `GET /mbooks-1/rest/book/movies/paging?setFirstResult=...&category=...`
  - `GET /mbooks-1/rest/book/movies/search?match=...&setFirstResult=...&category=...`

D) Reviews/ratings/community pages
- No backend API currently mapped in WebUI for:
  - movie reviews/comments
  - user ratings submission/history
  - celebrity content
  - blog/news feeds
- These should be P2+ and optional for booking MVP.

E) User profile/favorites pages
- Need explicit user endpoints if template sections are activated.
- Candidate service owner: `mbook-quarkus`.

---

## 4) Scope extension strategy

### Phase P1 (Booking-complete hardening)
Focus: make current routes production-stable.

- Keep only booking-related Film-Review pages active in navigation.
- Standardize contract docs for currently used endpoints.
- Add endpoint contract checks for WebUI-critical APIs.
- Ensure error shape consistency for `/login` and `/rest/book` calls.

Exit criteria:
- All current routes load without fallback/404.
- No missing endpoint for any current Angular controller in `app.js`.

### Phase P2 (Discovery enhancement)
Focus: improve movie discovery and template richness without social features.

- Add `trending-movies` endpoint usage on movies/home sections.
- Add movie-detail endpoint and wire detail page(s).
- Add server-side category/search/paging usage consistently.

Exit criteria:
- Discovery sections use backend data (not placeholders).
- API payload size/paging predictable for large catalogs.

### Phase P3 (Community/profile modules)
Focus: optional template modules.

- Add reviews, ratings, favorites, and profile endpoints.
- Add admin moderation endpoints only if UI module is enabled.

Exit criteria:
- Each enabled module has explicit endpoint contract + ownership.
- Disabled modules are removed from nav and bundle.

---

## 5) Service ownership map

- `dalogin-quarkus`: auth, session, checkout bridge, purchases management
- `mbooks-quarkus`: movies, venues, dates, seats, booking-facing catalog/discovery
- `mbook-quarkus`: user/profile domain (for future profile/favorites flows)
- `simple-service-webapp-quarkus`: static/media resource delivery

---

## 6) Deliverables for this planning feature

1. Endpoint matrix document (route -> controller -> endpoint -> service owner).
2. Gap list with P1/P2/P3 categorization.
3. Backend endpoint proposals for missing template sections.
4. Acceptance checklist for enabling/disabling template modules safely.

---

## 7) Acceptance criteria

- [ ] Every active Film-Review Angular route has at least one mapped backend endpoint.
- [ ] Every mapped endpoint has a declared owning backend service.
- [ ] Missing endpoints are categorized by phase (P1/P2/P3).
- [ ] Plan explicitly defines what stays in current booking scope vs future scope.
- [ ] `trending-movies` is listed as discovery extension for WebUI scope.

